On April 15, 2021, President Biden declared a national emergency due to the harmful foreign activities of the Russian government. These activities include undermining democratic elections, engaging in cyberattacks, using corruption to influence foreign governments, targeting dissidents and journalists, undermining security in important regions, and violating international law. The national emergency was expanded in scope on March 8, 2022, and additional steps were taken on August 20, 2021, March 11, 2022, and April 6, 2022. President Biden has decided to continue the national emergency for another year in accordance with the National Emergencies Act.